"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-10-transfer-three-deals-to-be-completed-after-2024-olympics-end\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  At least three transfer deals will be wrapped up after the men's football event ended at the 2024 Olympics.  Spain defeated hosts France 5-3 in the final played on Friday, with Sergio Camello scoring two goals in extra time to seal victory.  Attentions will now be turned to club football with the new season set to kick off.  Samu Omorodion, who was with the Spaniard team, will undergo his medicals with Chelsea and Amir Richardson will complete his move to Fiorentina.  Football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, wrote on X: \\\"Several deals are set to be completed after the end of the Olympics.  \\\"Samu Omorodion will sign seven year deal at Chelsea.  \\\"Amir Richardson, set to join Fiorentina for \\u20ac9m plus \\u20ac1m add-ons and sell-on.  \\\"Marc Pubill, Atalanta player for \\u20ac15m plus add-ons.\\\"  Zubairu appeals for more support for El-Kanemi Warriors  Paris 2024 Olympics: Reuben launches Nigeria's final search for medal  2024 Olympics: Minister John Enoh calls for reforms in sports administration  2024 Olympics: Tinubu celebrates Rena Wakama for winning 'Best Coach' prize  USA win 2024 Olympics, Kenya lead other African countries on medal table  2024 Olympics: Someone so tiny - Lacombe slams Messi over reaction to Argentina defeat  2024 Olympics: VAR drama as Argentina vs Morocco match restarts after 2hrs  CAS clears Amusan of doping violation offence ahead 2024 Olympics  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"